"use client" import { useState, useEffect } from "react" import "./DashboardPage.css" const DashboardPage = () => { const [orders, setOrders] = useState([]) const [stats, setStats] = useState({ totalOrders: 0, pendingOrders: 0, completedOrders: 0, todayOrders: 0, }) useEffect(() => { // Mock data for demo const mockOrders = [ { id: "ORD-001", patientName: "John Doe", medication: "Amoxicillin 500mg", dosage: "3 times daily", status: "pending", createdAt: "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z", }, { id: "ORD-002", patientName: "Jane Smith", medication: "Lisinopril 10mg", dosage: "Once daily", status: "completed", createdAt: "2024-01-15T09:15:00Z", }, { id: "ORD-003", patientName: "Bob Johnson", medication: "Metformin 850mg", dosage: "Twice daily", status: "processing", createdAt: "2024-01-15T11:45:00Z", }, ] setOrders(mockOrders) setStats({ totalOrders: mockOrders.length, pendingOrders: mockOrders.filter((o) => o.status === "pending").length, completedOrders: mockOrders.filter((o) => o.status === "completed").length, todayOrders: mockOrders.length, }) }, []) const getStatusClass = (status) => { switch (status) { case "pending": return "status-pending" case "processing": return "status-processing" case "completed": return "status-completed" default: return "status-default" } } return (
